    • Method Detail

      • Gameplay

        public void Gameplay()
        Parameters:
        GAWMax - Gets the Max Width Coordinate of the GameArena on the X-Axis
        GAHMax - Gets the Max Height Coordinate of the GameArena on the Y-Axis
        GAWMid - Calculates the Central Coordinate of the GameArena on the X-Axis
        GAHMid - Calculates the Central Coordinate of the GameArena on the Y-Axis
        GAWMin - Calculates the Minimum Coordinate of the GameArena on the X-Axis
        GAHMin - Calculates the Minimum Coordinate of the GameArena on the Y-Axis
        EdgesX - Calculates the space in the GameArena which is used for the boarders at the GAWMin and GAWMax and to Calculate the Play Area (PWMin & PWMax)
        EdgesY - Calculates the space in the GameArena which is used for the boarders at the GAHMin and GAHMax and to Calculate the Play Area (PHMin & PHMax)
        PWMax - Calculates the Playable Width Max Coordinate on the X-Axis Minus the Boarder (GAWMax-EdgesX)
        PHMAX - Calculates the Playable Width Max Coordinate on the Y-Axis Minus the Boarder (GAHMax-EdgesY)
        PWMid - Calculates the Central Coordinate of the Playable Area on the X-Axis (PWMax / 2)
        PHMid - Calculates the Central Coordinate of the Playable Area on the Y-Axis (PHMax /2)
        PWMin - Calculates the Minimum Coordinate of the Playable Area on the X-Axis
        PHMin - Calculates the Minimum Coordinate of the Playable Area on the Y-Axis
        Nboard - Creates a Rectangle to form a Border at the TOP of the GameArena
        Eboard - Creates a Rectangle to form a Border at the RIGHT of the GameArena
        Sboard - Creates a Rectangle to form a Border at the BOTTOM of the GameArena
        Wboard - Creates a Rectangle to form a Border at the LEFT of the GameArena
